             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was sent after the prisoner, and found him in the yard at the Bear and Ragged-staff Inn, in Smithfield, with the skins under his arm; I brought him to the warehouse, he said he was going to sell them to a Jew; he said it was the first time, he did not deny but they were his master's property.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I took up this bundle and thought it was my linen; I went to this inn, and when I came to open it, I found it was not my linen, and I was going to take it back.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17840915-150-verdict698" type="verdictDescription">
